[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/TestClassScannerTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Key changes:
[assistant] - Removed `@ClassTemplate` / `@ExtendWith(SpringExtension.class)` from the public `TestClassScannerTest`.
[assistant] - Added a nested disabled fixture class:
[assistant]   - `@Disabled("Fixture discovered by TestClassScannerTest")`
[assistant]   - `@ClassTemplate`
[assistant]   - `@ExtendWith({SpringExtension.class, ...})`
[assistant] - The scanner test still scans and asserts discovery of that fixture and its nested `@Nested` classes, so it should still reach `TestClassScanner.collectNestedTestClasses()` and `Class#getDeclaredClasses()` without executing `SpringExtension` lifecycle callbacks under the older JUnit runtime.
